        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(mattermost): accept legacy config compatibility keys",
        "body": "## Summary\n- accept legacy Mattermost `channelOverrides`, `sessionPolicy`, and `attachments` keys in the strict channel schema so upgraded configs no longer fail as additional properties\n- regenerate bundled channel config metadata so packaged config validation uses the same compatibility surface\n- keep account-scoped compatibility aligned with the top-level schema and exported Mattermost config types\n- add regression coverage for both extension schema parsing and `validateConfigObjectWithPlugins` bundled channel metadata validation\n\n## Testing\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.runtime-config.config.ts src/config/validation.channel-metadata.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node node_modules/vitest/vitest.extension-mattermost.config.ts extensions/mattermost/src/config-schema.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- generated metadata parse check confirmed legacy keys exist at both top-level and account scope\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: A Mattermost config migrated from older pre-plugin settings can keep `channelOverrides`, `sessionPolicy`, and `attachments` without being rejected by the packaged bundled-channel config validation path.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux at head `4c4883cc9a`, Node `v22.22.0`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.runtime-config.config.ts src/config/validation.channel-metadata.test.ts\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node node_modules/vitest/vitest.extension-mattermost.config.ts extensions/mattermost/src/config-schema.test.ts\ngit diff --check\nnode -e 'parse generated bundled channel metadata and assert Mattermost legacy keys exist at top-level and account scope'\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\nvalidation.channel-metadata.test.ts:\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  8 passed (8)\n\nconfig-schema.test.ts:\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  11 passed (11)\n\ngit diff --check\nexit status: 0\n\ngenerated metadata assertion:\n{ \"topLevel\": true, \"account\": true }\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: `validateConfigObjectWithPlugins` now accepts a `channels.mattermost` config containing legacy compatibility keys through bundled channel metadata, and the Mattermost extension schema accepts the same keys at top-level and account scope.\n- **What was not tested**: I did not connect to a live Mattermost server. A broad `tsgo` extension typecheck was attempted locally but hit unrelated current-worktree dependency/baseline diagnostics around `@openclaw/proxyline` and `src/plugin-sdk/file-lock.ts`, outside this PR's touched files.\n\nCloses #57618",
